1st:Question
Write a program to check whether a person is eligible for voting or not ?
ans:
object Voting{
    def main(args: Array[String]){
        var a: Int = 19
        if(a>=18)
        {
            println("yes")
        }
        else
        {
            println("No")
        }
    }
}

2nd:Question
Write a program to check whether a number entered by user is even or odd.
Ans:
object EV0D{
    def main(args: Array[String]){
        val x:Int = 35
        if(x%2==0)
        {
            println("even")
        }
        else
        {
            println("odd")
        }
    }
}

3rd Question
Write a program to check whether a number is divisible by 7 or not.
ans:
object div{
    def main(args: Array[String]){
        val x:Int = 35
        if(x%7==0)
        {
            println("True")
        }
        else
        {
            println("False")
        }
    }
}

4th Question:
Write a program to display "Hello" if a number entered by user is a multiple of five , otherwise print "Bye".
Ans:
object percent{
    def main(args:Array[String]):Unit={
      
  println("enter value")
        val x:Int = scala.io.StdIn.readInt()
        
        if (x%5==0)
        {
            println("hello")
        }
        else 
        {
            println("bye")
        }
    }
}

5th Question
Write a program to calculate the electricity bill (accept number of unit from user) according to the following criteria :
             Unit                                                     Price  
            First 100 units                                               no charge
            Next 100 units                                              Rs 5 per unit
            After 200 units                                             Rs 10 per unit
ans:
object ecb{
    def main(args:Array[String]):Unit={
      
  println("enter ecb")
        val ecb:Float = scala.io.StdIn.readFloat()
        
        if (ecb<=100)
        {
            println("no charge")
        }
        else if(ecb>100 && ecb<=200)
        {
            println(100*5)
        }
        else
        {
          val hplus=(100)*5
          val tplus=(ecb-200)*10
          println(hplus+tplus)
        }
    }
}

6th Question
6. Write a program to display the last digit of a number.
(hint : any number % 10 will return the last digit)
ans:
object last{
    def main(args:Array[String]):Unit={
      
  println("enter value")
        val x:Int = scala.io.StdIn.readInt()
        println(x%10)
    }
}
7TH Question
Write a program to check whether the last digit of a number( entered by user ) is 
divisible by 3 or not.
object lastdig{
    def main(args:Array[String]):Unit={
      
  println("enter value")
        val x:Int = scala.io.StdIn.readInt()
        val y= (x%10)
       
        if  (y%3==0)
        {
        println("true")
        }
        else
        {
        println("false")
        }
    }
}

8th Question
8. Write a program to accept percentage from the user and display the grade according to the following criteria:

         Marks                                    Grade
         > 90                                         A
         > 80 and <= 90                        B
         >= 60 and <= 80                     C
         below 60                                   D
ans:
object percent{
    def main(args:Array[String]):Unit={
      
  println("enter percentage marks")
        val per:Float = scala.io.StdIn.readFloat()
        
        if (per>90)
        {
            println("grade A")
        }
        else if(per>80 && per<=90)
        {
            println("grade B")
        }
        else if (per>60 && per<= 80)
        {
            println("grade c")
        }
        else
        {
            println("grade D")
        }
    }
}

Write a program to accept the cost price of a bike and display the road tax to be paid according to the following criteria :

        Cost price (in Rs)                                       Tax
        > 100000                                                  15 %
        > 50000 and <= 100000                           10%
        <= 50000                                                  5% 
ans:
object tax{
    def main(args:Array[String]):Unit={
      
  println("enter tax")
        val ta:Float = scala.io.StdIn.readFloat()
        
        if (ta> 100000 )
        {
            println("15%")
        }
        else if(ta>50000 && ta<=100000)
        {
            println("10%")
        }
        else
        {
            println("grade 5%")
        }
    }
}
10. Write a program to check whether an years is leap year or not.  
ans:
object percent{
    def main(args:Array[String]):Unit={
      
  println("enter value")
        val x:Int = scala.io.StdIn.readInt()
        
        if (x%4==0)
        {
            println("leap year")
        }
        else 
        {
            println("not a leap year")
        }
    }
}
